objectives:
Multivariate time series forecasting is an important machine learning problem across many domains, including the prediction of energy output or consumption patterns, health care outcomes, climate modelling, financial trading, or the monitoring of critical engineering equipment. The temporal data arising in these real-world applications often involves a mixture of long-term and short-term patterns, for which traditional approaches such as autoregressive models and Gaussian Process may fail. This research project will address the study and development of deep learning approaches for time series forecasting.

Goals: 

- Study deep learning methods for multivariate time series forecasting, based on convolutional and/or recurrent neural networks;
- Development and evaluation (e.g., using data from case studies in health variable monitoring) of novel deep learning methods for multivariate time series forecasting;

References:

